page.title: 20FELLDYKE CAR PARK LAMPLUGH
page.content: The Felldyke car park was built in 1985 to allow access for the people who go into the Cogra Moss and Blake area. It is used by people who: have day tickets for fishing, are going for walks, are riding with Kerbeck Ponies, are interested in the wild life to be found. The car park means it is much easier for the keen fishermen/women and fell walkers and runners to get close to an area where they want to be. People who walk enjoy the fells and forestry. When walking they wear strong shoes or boots and clothing suitable for the weather. If they are going out for quite a while they take a rucksack. The fells are open land, there are a few footpaths and sheep trods. Since the car park has been opened it has often been full.
